Suppose array is given and k value is also given.
arr-> 2 3 5 2 9 7 1
k-> 3

So basicaly we find the subarray of length 3 and find the maximum sum from the subarray.
Sub array of the given array whose size is 3 is:
        Sum
2 3 5-> 10
3 5 2-> 10
5 2 9-> 16
2 9 7-> 18
9 7 1-> 17
Return the maximum as 18.
So, how we code it?

Brute Force Approach.
arr->  2  3 5 2 9 7 1
Loop inside loop . for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++)
                    {
                        for(int j=i;j<i+k;j++)
                        {
                        // sum nikal k maximum ko update krta rhunga.
                      }

So, how we can make it efficient?
How we can check wheteher we can make it more efficient or not? So, we have to check these things
1) Whether I am doing any repeatitive work in program?

Where we can use sliding window?
